latestIgtvVideos.title: Conscious nursery for Baby B! Repost from @indiatoday_home
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
When Bahaar Dhawan Rohatgi @bahaar_art found out she was going to be a mom, she was over the moon. She knew her baby’s nursery had to be special. So, not only did she paint the walls with beautiful art, but also ensured that the nursery is sustainable and eco-friendly. To know more watch this nursery tour with a difference. 

She used Upcycled Cot & chair, painted & created her own wall paper, paintings, frames for paintings & light installation made by Bahaar were framed with leftover fabric, she designed the rug & added tables made from resin & reclaimed wood. #InHouseB #bahaarart

latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Part A: Immortal Love : The Muse 
Part B: Loving yourself indefinitely 
Artists often find themselves oscillating between two stages in life. Sometimes, we go deep, at other times- we let go & set ourselves free. 
Had this sitting in my phone archives for a while, but decided to share this because I’m sure somebody needs to be reminded about the evolution of a caterpillar🐛to a butterfly🦋🍁🤎👩‍🎨💜🎴🧡 #loveyourself Indefinitely 💕🖊 .

latestIgtvVideos.title: ‘Covid Ka Irada’ x @bahaar_art 🎧
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Each frame 🖼 is from my artworks. Please listen to it with #suspensionofdisbelief for it’s an artistic expression. 
In the last few weeks, I have felt a gamut of emotions as we continue to collectively deal with an unprecedented situation, a known enemy, or so we think. #coronavirus continues to operate in abstraction, the presence couldn’t be more evident but the form, completely unknown- forever transforming, evolving, transmitting. The visuals are supplemented by lines I penned from ‘Covid Ka Irada’ (Covid’S Intention) - which is rife with sarcasm, irritation, dismay, empathy, sympathy, gratitude, wisdom, patience and finally hope, reflecting the state of mind, at different points of time.  Perhaps, Covid is ensuring, there are lessons to be learnt before we sleep. .
.
#bahaarart #art #artist #paint #texture #bdsmusings #covid #covıd19 #indianartist #abstraction #abstractionist #visualart #urdu #hindustani #visualartist

latestIgtvVideos.title: R.I.P. Irrfan Khan Process Video dated 29.04.20 as promised
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
PORTRAITS aren’t my thing, (especially realism) Impressionism and abstraction is - so this one is bordering distorted abstraction and reality, just how lunchbox made me feel. Irrfan Khan’s work, struggle, resilience, demeanour always inspired me: a perfect subject for an impressionist. For someone who can’t sit though a movie unless it’s worth its while, I’ve sat like a permanent fixture through all his performances because there is no one more real than him. Grateful for your overwhelming response on my stories 🙏🏼 Blending & finishing took few more hours which isn’t part of the video. Hope the tips will help you create using limited supplies💜
.
.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Have we forgotten how to love?! 💔
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Recorded this video on 31st March (seems ancient now) Insomnia 👀 x terrible angles: Wasn’t meant for my Instagram obviously 🙄, but words of encouragement from insta fam & friends on my 3am PJ poetry recitals have given me the courage. Thank you 
#ibtidaindia for pushing me to do this 💜 yes I will work on the ‘Kh’ from the epiglottis 🤦🏻‍♀️
‘Tujh se ho kar khafa hum khud se khafa rehne lage, 
Tanha na reh jaaye, isliye sab se mohabbat karne lage. 
Teri aankhon ne kuch aur hi kaha tha 
hamse : 
Khub laga lo pehre, raste rab khole! 
Tum to aaye the meri tanhaai baantne, mujhe khush dekh, tum khud hi khafa ho chal diye! 
Tere ishq se behad narazagi hai hamein, 
Phool Khushboo se khafa ho jaise. 
Tujh se ho kar khafa hum khud se khafa rehne lage’. -  بہار
Bahaar 
Repost from @ibtida_ek_mehfil_ Have we forgotten to love?  @bahaar_art with this beautiful narrative on love and belonging .
.

👗✨ Design it, but don’t forget to protect it!
Did you know? Under Section 15(2) of the Indian Copyright Act, if a designer’s unregistered design is applied to more than 50 pieces of a product, copyright protection automatically ceases.

That means unless your design is registered under the Designs Act, 2000, you could lose the right to take legal action—even if someone blatantly copies your work.

Just ask the courts. Even iconic designers have lost lawsuits because of this fine print.

📌 Designers, artists, product creators—protect your IP before you mass-produce. Don’t let the law become the loophole.

As a lawyer, artist, and creator who works with countless designers and enjoys fashion, I felt it was my duty to spread this awareness.
Sometimes being creative is not enough—knowing the law of the land is key to thriving as a creative professional and running a smooth business.

#DesignLaw #IntellectualProperty #IndianCopyrightAct #DesignsAct #FashionLaw #KnowYourRights #Section15 #IPAwareness #FashionDesignersIndia #ProtectYourWork #CreativeBusiness #LawForCreators #ArtistLife #BuildAndProtect
